Project Summery - \
	This Python project utilizes the turtle graphics library to build a classic, 30-second Whack-a-Mole arcade game played on a 3x3 grid. It features a gameplay loop where players click randomly appearing moles that speed up over time to increase difficulty. Additionally, the game implements persistent data storage using text files to save player names and display a top-5 leaderboard at the end of the match.\
